# Draculoides warramboo

| synonyms =
}}
Draculoides warramboo is a species of schizomid arachnids (commonly known as sprickets or short-tailed whip-scorpions) in the Hubbardiidae family. It is endemic to Australia. It was described in 2020 by Australian arachnologists Kym Abrams and Mark Harvey.
Distribution and habitat
The species occurs in the arid Pilbara region of North West Western Australia. The type locality is Warramboo, about 50 km west of the iron-ore mining town of Pannawonica and some 1,400 km north of Perth.
